article.headline: Gottstein goes down with ankle injury, but Eagles roll
article.linkText: No. 19 Boston College wins despite losing top scorer
article.story:
NEW ORLEANS (AP) -- Clare Droesch scored 16 points and Kim Mackie
added 11 as Boston College (No. 19 ESPN/USA Today; No. 20 Associated Press) beat Southern Methodist 67-57 in the first round
of the DoubleTree Classic on Saturday.

	   Boston College (7-2) won without leading scorer Becky Gottstein,
who sprained her left ankle five minutes into the game. Gottstein
is doubtful for the championship game Sunday against Tulane.

	   The Eagles led 29-25 at the half after shooting 43 percent
(13-for-30) from the field. SMU (5-4) hit just 32 percent (9-for-28)
before the break.

	   SMU outrebounded Boston College 42-38. Shanta Ramdhanny had nine
rebounds for SMU and Andrea Cossey had eight.

	   Jessalyn Deveny scored 10 points for the Eagles and Brianne
Stephenson scored seven points and had seven assists. Mackie and
Deveny each had six rebounds.

	   Cossey led SMU with 16 points, and Ramdhanny and Alisa Wright
scored 10 each. Ramdhanny also had five assists.

	   Tulane beat North Carolina-Greensboro 63-43 in the other
first-round game Saturday.
